Simple picture: •  Low frequency (standard GWs) → continuum limit, v = c, no dispersion. •  High frequency → lattice “graininess” → phase velocity v_ph(ω) < c, small correction. •  Correction term: v_ph(ω) ≈ c (1 - (ω_Pl / ω)^2) for ω << ω_Pl (weak dispersion).
